{
 "name": "prepend-leak-2019",
 "title": "Route-optimizer leak — June 2019",
 "description": "A BGP optimizer at a small Pennsylvania ISP generated fake more-specifics of Cloudflare prefixes; a customer — a steel company, AS396531 — leaked them to Verizon (AS701), which propagated them worldwide. Long, strange AS paths and rerouted traffic everywhere.",
